173 (1) 'Hazardous substance' shall have the same meaning as set forth in Code
174 Section 12-8-92.
175 (2) 'Weapon' shall have the same meaning as set forth in Code Section 16-5-44.1. Such
176 term shall include, but shall not be limited to, each item included in paragraph (4) of
177 subsection (a) of Code Section 16-11-127.1.
178 (b) A person commits the offense of a terroristic threat of a school when he or she
179 threatens to commit any crime of violence, release any hazardous substance, or burn or
180 damage property and such threat is made:
181 (1) With the purpose of terrorizing another who at the time of such threat is physically
182 present:
183 (A) On public or private school operated property, including, but not limited to, school
184 buildings and school grounds;
185 (B) On a school bus or other vehicle furnished by a public or private school for the
186 transportation of students; or
187 (C) At a public or private school sponsored activity;
188 (2) With the purpose of causing the evacuation of:
189 (A) Public or private school operated property, including, but not limited to, school
190 buildings and school grounds; or
191 (B) A school bus or other vehicle furnished by a public or private school for the
192 transportation of students; or
193 (3) In reckless disregard of the risk of causing the terror or evacuation described in
194 paragraph (1) or (2) of this subsection.
195 (c) A person commits the offense of a terroristic act upon a school when he or she commits
196 an act of using a weapon or flaming symbol or flambeau, releasing any hazardous
197 substance or any simulated hazardous substance under the guise of a hazardous substance,
198 or, while not in the commission of a lawful act, shooting at or throwing an object at a
