215 (d)(1) A person convicted of the offense of a terroristic threat of a school shall be
216 punished as for a misdemeanor; provided, however, that, if the threat suggested the death
217 of any person, the person shall be guilty of a felony and upon conviction thereof shall be
218 punished by a fine of not more than $1,000.00, imprisonment for not less than one nor
219 more than five years, or both; and provided, further, that, if any person suffers a serious
220 physical injury as a direct result of a threat giving rise to a conviction under
221 subsection (b) of this Code section, the person shall be guilty of a felony and upon
222 conviction thereof shall be punished by a fine of not more than $250,000.00,
223 imprisonment for not less than five nor more than 40 years, or both.
224 (2) A person convicted of the offense of a terroristic act upon a school shall be guilty of
225 a felony and upon conviction thereof shall be punished by a fine of not more
