232 SECTION 5.
233 Said chapter is further amended by revising Code Section 20-2-1185, relating to school
234 safety plans and drills, as follows:
235 "20-2-1185.
236 (a) As used in this Code section, the term 'site threat assessment' means conducting an
237 evaluation for purposes of most effectively preventing, reducing, or responding to threats
238 of violence, mass casualty incidents and other acts of terrorism, natural disasters, and
239 hazardous materials accidents.
240 (b)(1) By June 1 of each year, each public school in this state shall have performed a site
241 threat assessment of its buildings, facilities, and campuses by a law enforcement agency
242 or other appropriate government agency or by an individual or entity certified and
243 approved pursuant to paragraph (2) of this subsection. Such site threat assessment shall
244 inform the preparation and maintenance of a school safety plan as provided for in
245 subsection (c) of this Code section.
246 (2) The Georgia Emergency Management and Homeland Security Agency shall be
247 exclusively authorized to certify and approve private individuals and entities to provide
248 site threat assessments to public schools in this state. Beginning January 1, 2026, the
249 Georgia Emergency Management and Homeland Security Agency shall maintain a list
250 of individuals and entities that are certified and approved for purposes of this Code
251 section to provide site threat assessments to public schools.
